    "headline": "CrowdStrike, Salesforce could be AI winners, market expert says",
    "summary": "<body><p>STORY: \"The winners will be software companies that integrate AI into their offerings,\" said Kampitsis, who sees undervalued opportunities in the space.</p><p>He pointed to cybersecurity names including CrowdStrike and Palo Alto Networks as companies that are integrating AI into their offerings, saying they \"represent an opportunity.\"</p><p>Kampitsis said another \"opportunity with upside\" was Salesforce, which he called an artificial intelligence company of its own.</p><p>\"We think there's a lot of potential upside there for an investor looking to take a chance on a real opportunity,\" he said.</p><p>Salesforce forecast second-quarter revenue below Wall Street estimates on Wednesday despite a stronger-than-expected first quarter.</p></body>",
